epi-PAR.def: The PARI indicator measures ecological representativeness as the proportion of biologically scaled environmental diversity included in a country‚Äôs terrestrial protected areas. The measure relies on remote sensing, biodiversity informatics, and global modeling of fine-scaled variation in biodiversity composition for plant, vertebrate, and invertebrate species.
